    ## Configurable options

    Option | Description | Type | Default value
    --- | --- | ---
    content | array of items to populate the list | Ember.A() | null
    selected | pass in an initial selection | Object | null
    optionLabelKey | the item property to use as the visible label in the menu | string | 'title'
    optionDisabledKey | optionally provide a boolean item property to use a flag for disabling menu items | string, null | null
    prompt | prompt text for the main input | string | 'Select an option'
    searchPrompt | prompt text for the search input | string | 'Type to search'
    noResultsMessage | message to display if a filter produces no results | string | 'No matching results'
    limitSearchToWordBoundary | when set to true, search will only match the beginning of words | boolean | true
    sortBy | provide an options item key to sort the list by | boolean | false
    isCreatable | when true, a create button is available to create the search text | boolean | false
    createLabel | prompt to show beside the create button | string | 'Create'
    createMatchCaseInsensitive | when true, the create button will hide if the search text matches an option, case insensitive. When false the search text must match an option exactly to hide the create button | boolean | false
    on-create | Specify your own named action to trigger when the create button is clicked. eg. <code>(action "create")</code> | Ember action | Ember.K
    isClearable | when true, a clear button is available to clear the selection | boolean | true
    clearLabel | prompt to show beside the clear button for a clearable menu | string | 'Clear selection'
    on-change | Specify your own named action to trigger when the search text  changes. eg. <code>(action "update")</code> The search text is sent as an argument. | Ember action | Ember.K
    on-search | Specify your own named action to trigger when the search text  changes. eg. <code>(action "update")</code>The search text is sent as an argument. Useful for custom filtering or AJAX search. Note that internal filter is automatically disabled when an on-search action is provided. | Ember action | Ember.K
    isLoading | pass in your own boolean flag to toggle visibility of a loading animation | boolean | false
    loadingMessage | customize the text displayed beside the loading animation | string | 'Searching...'

